{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/projects/lead-to-read-website","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Lead to Read is an awesome non-profit based out of Kansas City that facilitates reading based mentorship in the Kansas City metro area. They connect adult volunteers with 1st-3rd grade students for one hour each week to read together. As their motto goes, “Together we are creating a community of readers, one lunch hour at a time.”</p>\n<p>I worked with Pauly Hart and Martha Conradt to give refresh the UI using Gatsby, while keeping Wordpress as the CMS.</p>\n<h2 id=\"motivations-for-the-redesign\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#motivations-for-the-redesign\" aria-label=\"motivations for the redesign permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Motivations for the redesign</h2>\n<p>Lead to Read is an awesome organization, but their previous website was… less than awesome. It’s a 10+ year old Wordpress site with less-than-glamorous Lighthouse audit scores:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/e4900/ltr_lighthouse.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.72972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Old Lead to Read website Lighthouse Scores\"\n        title=\"Old Lead to Read website Lighthouse Scores\"\n        src=\"/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/fcda8/ltr_lighthouse.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/12f09/ltr_lighthouse.png 148w,\n/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/e4a3f/ltr_lighthouse.png 295w,\n/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/fcda8/ltr_lighthouse.png 590w,\n/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/efc66/ltr_lighthouse.png 885w,\n/static/fc1e33dd239c1766827a53507a385b59/e4900/ltr_lighthouse.png 988w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The performance and accessibility categories are especially concerning: the site isn’t accessible or mobile friendly, and takes over 17 seconds to become interactive.</p>\n<p>I kept some “north star” goals in mind during the redesign:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Performance - improve those lighthouse scores.</li>\n<li>Accessible - make sure the site works for <em>everyone</em>.</li>\n<li>Responsive - a layout that works on any screen size.</li>\n<li>Approachable - clear messaging and easy-to-discover content.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-i-approached-the-design\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-i-approached-the-design\" aria-label=\"how i approached the design permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How I approached the design</h2>\n<p>Before starting, I combed the existing site and tried to group the existing content into more logically sections.</p>\n<p>After some sketching on paper, I used Sketch to bring mock out the proposed redesign:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/72e01/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 218.24324324324326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"New site design mocks\"\n        title=\"New site design mocks\"\n        src=\"/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/1c72d/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/a80bd/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg 148w,\n/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/1c91a/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg 295w,\n/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/1c72d/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg 590w,\n/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/a8a14/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg 885w,\n/static/cc168f7e768940c5d1a9f49df5bf872d/72e01/lead_to_read_sketch.jpg 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After a couple iterations and resolving feedback from Martha and Pauly, we settled on the landing page layout and navigation menu.</p>\n<p>Time for some coding!</p>\n<h2 id=\"project-structure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#project-structure\" aria-label=\"project structure permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Project structure</h2>\n<p>I created a new Gatsby site with the following plugins:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">gatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>plugin<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>sass <span class=\"token comment\">// enable SASS</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>transformer<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>sharp <span class=\"token comment\">// image processing</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>plugin<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>sharp <span class=\"token comment\">// image processing</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>plugin<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>typescript <span class=\"token comment\">// enable TS</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>plugin<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>offline<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// enable offline mode</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>source<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>filesystem <span class=\"token comment\">// make Gatsby aware of image assets</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>plugin<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>typography <span class=\"token comment\">// enable Typography.js</span>\ngatsby<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>source<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>wordpress <span class=\"token comment\">// the workhorse! Source content from WP.</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Beyond that, I decided to use mobile-first styling for all CSS, and defined a central defs.scss to be the single source of colors, spacing and mixins for the project. DRY!</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/e-nichols/f979c6c285643f6935581a320afc73ba.js\"></script>\n<h2 id=\"image-carousel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#image-carousel\" aria-label=\"image carousel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Image Carousel</h2>\n<h2 id=\"working-with-wordpress\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#working-with-wordpress\" aria-label=\"working with wordpress permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Working with Wordpress</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>normalizer</li>\n<li>routes to include</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"firebase-w-a-custom-domain\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#firebase-w-a-custom-domain\" aria-label=\"firebase w a custom domain permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Firebase w/ a custom domain</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Really easy.</li>\n<li>But sounds like cloud functions could use some more love. Not efficient. Link to Medium post.</li>\n<li>Is it… worth it?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"some-react-tidbits\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#some-react-tidbits\" aria-label=\"some react tidbits permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Some React tidbits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>OnLoad callback for imgs</li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":2,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#motivations-for-the-redesign\">Motivations for the redesign</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#how-i-approached-the-design\">How I approached the design</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#project-structure\">Project structure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#image-carousel\">Image Carousel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#working-with-wordpress\">Working with Wordpress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#firebase-w-a-custom-domain\">Firebase w/ a custom domain</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/projects/lead-to-read-website/#some-react-tidbits\">Some React tidbits</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/gatsby/","/tags/react/","/tags/firebase/"]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Lead to Read website redesign with Gatsby and Firebase","tags":["Gatsby","React","Firebase"],"date":"2020-04-04T00:12:03.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/lead-to-read-website"}}}